         <abstract>
            <p>An explicit version of the inversive congruential method with power of two modulus for generating uniform pseudorandom numbers is introduced. Statistical independence properties of the generated sequences are studied by means of the serial test. The method of proof relies on a detailed analysis of certain exponential sums.</p>
          </abstract>
